The paper proposes a self-supervised method for learning spatial-temporal representations from videos, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and multimedia (MM) research. The method involves generating blanks and options, which can be seen as a form of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). The paper also mentions the use of 3D-CNNs, which are a type of deep learning model commonly used in CV and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Finally, the paper evaluates the method on action recognition and video retrieval tasks, which are common applications in CV and MM. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.MM, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
